reviews.review_text: 25 years... ...later but still one of the best shows I ever saw. THIS recording is better than the official release.

Agreed... I agree with Ole Uncle John that this is far superior to the official release. As a Richmonder myself (sorry about the cops, everyone...and yes, I'm afraid they are still a disgrace) and a relative latecomer (i.e. post-Richmond) to the Dead, I had been excited to hear this legendary show, but after hearing DP21 I couldn't help but wonder what all the fuss was about. I don't wonder anymore. Listen to this tape, and you'll really understand what went on here that night. The band and the audience were locked in; the audience explosions on Little Red Rooster and Jack Straw and the sustained applause at the beginning of Saint are almost as breathtaking as the music itself, and the Dead seemed to thrive on it. Lots of tension in the air, and that tension got transmuted into great music. Absolutely essential.

one of the best shows I saw this is one of my top 2 shows I went to.
the other was 3/27/88 Hampton.

Jerry was on and everybody followed him. I drove up from the Columbia Halloween show which I thought was so so at best.
From the Dancing In The Streets until the Gloria 2nd set closer this show kicked ass! Dayjob encore... well it wasn't a perfect night.
The transitions between songs are tantalizing.
I am so glad I was there!
